%% View 3 — Trigger, admission, retry (draw.io swimlane / sequence)
sequenceDiagram
  participant CM as Control-M
  participant AC as Admission / concurrency gate
  participant Batch as AWS Batch
  participant Job as Spring Batch job
  participant PG as PostgreSQL

  CM->>AC: Request run (feed, s3 key, load_event_id)
  alt At global concurrency limit
    AC-->>CM: Defer / queue / fail fast per policy
  else Slot available
    AC->>Batch: Submit job
    Batch->>Job: Start container
    Job->>PG: Begin load_event + BATCH metadata
    Job->>PG: Chunk writes RECORD + PERSISTENCE
    alt Success
      Job->>PG: Terminal status COMPLETED*
      Job-->>Batch: Exit 0
    else Retryable failure
      Job->>PG: Mark FAILED / leave chunk state
      Batch-->>CM: Retry per policy (Batch + Control-M)
    else Replay
      CM->>AC: New run with new job params / run id
      AC->>Batch: Submit (idempotent keys prevent dup business writes)
    end
  end
